Installed rustc 1.91.1
And a nice 'rustup doc' command to get some local docs

rustc compiles the .rs file into an exe file, and it includes a pdb file by default

Standard stuff like a main function, functions start with fn, styling adds a space before the open curly bracket and it's on the same line as the function declaration.

println! is actually a macro, indicated by the !.

Rust's build system and package manager is called Cargo. Packages of code are referred to as crates.
Starting a new project with 'cargo new <project name>' creates a new folder with a .tml file.
The project can then be build or build and ran with 'cargo build' or 'cargo run'.
'cargo check' can be used to see if it would compile, without actually compiling it.
